1
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:42,660
What's going on?!

2
00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:45,540
I just heard a loud noise from over this way!

3
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:46,920
What was it?!

4
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,290
Is this what it was?

5
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,720
What happened?

6
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:57,930
S-Sir Bobbin!

7
00:01:57,930 --> 00:01:59,830
What happened to the wall?

8
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:05,640
What happened here?

9
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:05,640
Who did this?

10
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:07,790
It's not important.

11
00:02:07,790 --> 00:02:08,900
B-But–

12
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:11,610
You guys can stay here.

13
00:02:14,820 --> 00:02:15,990
Sir Bobbin...

14
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:30,830
Don't worry about this.

15
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:34,210
I'll dispose of the problem myself.

16
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:38,800
That guy will never ever get away with this!

17
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:41,800
Even the demons of hell...

18
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:44,720
ascend to the earth...

19
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:47,180
to attend Mama's tea party!

20
00:02:55,070 --> 00:02:57,750
Mirror, mirror! Thank you!

21
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:59,400
You're welcome!

22
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,360
Hey...

23
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:01,360
Huh?

24
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:06,360
Something big is... enveloping Brook...

25
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,420
No way...

26
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:19,970
I can't believe this...

27
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:26,470
That place is...

28
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:31,060
What are you gonna do?

29
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,770
That room is...

30
00:03:37,310 --> 00:03:40,930
our Mama's bedroom!

31
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:43,510
One of the Four Emperors, Big Mom?!

32
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,290
W-W-What should we do?

33
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:48,950
Well, at least he's alive...

34
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:53,370
– Brook...
– I didn't expect him to be in a place like that.

35
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:59,340
But, why is she sleeping
with Brook cradled in her arms?

36
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:04,720
– He's passed out, too.
– How in the world can he sleep?!

37
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,260
Wake up, Brook!

38
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:13,770
No good. He doesn't hear you.

39
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,700
Mama would never willingly allow you

40
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,820
to take such a strange, bony creature!

41
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,900
But don't worry.

42
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:26,070
I can make it so she loosens her grip on him.

43
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,910
Mama! It's me, Brûlée!

44
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:30,910
Choo!

45
00:04:30,910 --> 00:04:32,710
– Help!
– Choo!

46
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:35,340
Cut it out!

47
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,340
Cover their mouths!

48
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:36,720
Electro!

49
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:48,060
Did all of that wake Big Mom up?

50
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,140
Oh, good. She's still sleeping...

51
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:59,190
She... She...

52
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:01,570
She spotted us!

53
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:12,270
Oh, it's just a fly.

54
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:27,260
No! What, what? What's wrong?!

55
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,010
He woke up!

56
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:31,540
Brook! Over here, over here!

57
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,180
Come to us now!

58
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:35,980
Brook! Brook! Brook!

59
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:39,480
Oh, it's just a fly.

60
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,530
Don't go back to sleep!

61
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:46,400
What is it, Mama?
Are we under attack?

62
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,030
I'm sleeping!

63
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:50,120
Damn you!

64
00:05:52,410 --> 00:05:53,870
There you are!

65
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:25,940
They're so powerful!

66
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:41,130
How are we supposed...

67
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,420
to save...

68
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:45,590
...Brook...

69
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:48,590
...from those monsters?!

70
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,020
Hey! Stop!

71
00:07:03,650 --> 00:07:05,230
This isn't for you!

72
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:19,200
I'm sorry. There's somebody
that I really want to give it to.

73
00:07:30,910 --> 00:07:32,220
Hmm...

74
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,790
Does it need more hair?

75
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:37,540
Hmm, then, will this work?

76
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,680
Yeah, that'll work perfectly!

77
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,940
Where exactly did you find this stuff?

78
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:44,360
I found it at the castle's execution grounds.

79
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:47,260
And some seaweed from the kitchen
is a substitute for his afro.

80
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:50,320
Okay, it's done.

81
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:54,030
Oh! It looks just like Brook!

82
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:55,030
Definitely!

83
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,450
If we can switch him out with this thing...

84
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,290
she won't realize that we've taken Brook away!

85
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:08,050
Now, if we place Brûlée
 right on the mirror,

86
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:12,670
we can come and go through it freely.

87
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,970
Damn! I'll make them pay for this!

88
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:21,260
I think it's all set now. Let's begin.

89
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:24,520
The Brook Rescue Mission!

90
00:08:29,570 --> 00:08:31,490
Okay, I'm gonna try!

91
00:08:31,490 --> 00:08:33,390
Be careful, Chobro!

92
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:36,450
I know! You can just count on me!

93
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,650
You idiot!

94
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:17,520
That was scary! Really scary!

95
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,330
Are you okay, Chobro?

96
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:21,440
Somebody else should try.

97
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:24,710
Okay, I'll try next.

98
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:37,180
That's it!

99
00:09:37,690 --> 00:09:40,140
Brook... Brook, wake up.

100
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:42,130
Hey, Brook, wake up now.

101
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:44,390
Oh, no! The snot bubble's coming!

102
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,480
Run!

103
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:55,610
Did she notice...

104
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:58,280
Staaare...

105
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,030
It's staring right at me...

106
00:10:08,330 --> 00:10:09,290
Is that...

107
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:11,090
...a stuffed bunny?!

108
00:10:11,090 --> 00:10:12,840
That's not gonna work!

109
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:20,500
Oh, it's just a stuffed bunny.

110
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:24,100
What? That worked?

111
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,810
Now's your chance, Carrot!

112
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:30,140
I'll do it this time...

113
00:10:39,690 --> 00:10:41,750
Is that fly still here?

114
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:45,840
What an annoying fly!

115
00:10:53,540 --> 00:10:56,550
That was scary! Really scary!

116
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:57,900
Uh-huh.

117
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,780
Now we need someone else to try.

118
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:02,800
How disappointing.
I guess when it comes to things like this,

119
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:05,260
I must be the one to do it!

120
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,320
Brook!

121
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,800
Hey, wake up!

122
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:21,230
Brook!

123
00:11:27,010 --> 00:11:28,620
She's rolling over!

124
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,130
That's good for us.

125
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:38,380
Big Mom isn't holding him anymore.

126
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,310
Okay, I'll try!

127
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,430
Brook, wake up!

128
00:11:51,770 --> 00:11:53,190
Brook!

129
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,480
It's me, Brook!

130
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:01,240
A ghost!

131
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:05,200
What is it?

132
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,370
Are you still here?

133
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,920
Oh, no!

134
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:16,130
You annoying fly!

135
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,760
Heavenly...

136
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:22,880
Feuer!

137
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:37,820
Yes!

138
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:37,820
We did it!

139
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,240
That... That was close.

140
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:49,120
Thank you, Jinbe!

141
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,880
Mission: Successful!

142
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,830
Yahoo!

143
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:58,520
– This is great!
– I'm so relieved!

144
00:12:57,170 --> 00:12:58,520
Huh?

145
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:33,470
It seems like he created quite a ruckus.

146
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:51,890
This is it for him!

147
00:13:53,430 --> 00:13:58,650
We're currently holding Straw Hat Luffy
and the Cat Burglar captive-nasu.

148
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:03,690
He fought against one of their
top officers all night to get this far!

149
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:05,550
So his body is–

150
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,180
But...

151
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:12,370
you said you'd be waiting for me right here!

152
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,710
Where are you, Luffy?!

153
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,850
Luffy!

154
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:35,720
Y...

155
00:14:36,270 --> 00:14:36,680
Y...

156
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:37,810
Y...

157
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:40,810
You startled me!

158
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:41,980
A...

159
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:43,020
A...

160
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,570
A...

161
00:14:44,990 --> 00:14:47,360
And all of this happened!

162
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,700
No, you're the one who startled me !

163
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:52,910
A ghost!

164
00:14:52,910 --> 00:14:55,910
You screamed at a very bad time!

165
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,870
Thank you very much.

166
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:01,980
In any case, you're alive.
That's all that matters.

167
00:15:01,980 --> 00:15:05,120
Yes, I thought I was going to die!

168
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,170
I am dead...

169
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:15,260
I should've realized
when I saw their heavy security...

170
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:19,090
just how impossible it would be for us
to get a copy of the lode poneglyph.

171
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:23,900
But I pushed it,
and put your life in danger.

172
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,400
I'm sorry!

173
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:31,160
What are you saying?
Everything you did was for us!

174
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,870
Like you said before,

175
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:40,080
since we were infiltrating them as a two-man team,
it was a golden opportunity.

176
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:44,590
If we had attempted to steal Big Mom's lode poneglyph at any other time,

177
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:49,050
there would've been no way
to avoid an all-out pirate war!

178
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:55,850
That's why we had to try,
even if the odds were stacked against us.

179
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:03,980
Here are the rubbings.

180
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:09,320
But, anyway, Pedro-san,
I can't believe you got away safely too.

181
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,360
Rubbing...?

182
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,650
What?!

183
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:18,160
I was so desperate for ideas that I couldn't
come up with anything but that decoy plan...

184
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:22,580
Wait a minute, Brook! Don't tell me this is...

185
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:25,370
Those are the poneglyph rubbings.

186
00:16:26,190 --> 00:16:28,550
It was such a close call!

187
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:32,090
Just when I'd finished with the third sheet,

188
00:16:32,090 --> 00:16:35,180
Big Mom herself burst into the room!

189
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:42,560
You actually got it?!

190
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:50,610
You were against all those guards,
and there was even a sweet commander there...

191
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,700
and yet, you came out with Big Mom's poneglyph,

192
00:16:56,700 --> 00:17:01,440
something that any of the other emperors
would kill to have?!

193
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,620
You really...

194
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,750
Um, yes.

195
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:12,670
– What?!
– What?!

196
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:16,640
He stole our poneglyph?!

197
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:19,350
Brook!

198
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,720
This is amazing!

199
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,440
It's a miracle!

200
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:32,440
Even Big Mom's family members are not easily
permitted access to the treasure repository.

201
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:34,570
You're really something!

202
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:37,200
Then, if I could just see your panties–

203
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,930
Quit it!

204
00:17:38,930 --> 00:17:41,080
His bones got broken again!

205
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:44,860
Well, that's one of our goals out of the way!

206
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:48,250
All we have to do now is take Sanji and run!

207
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:35,380
What?!

208
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:37,140
Neither of them are there?!

209
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:38,460
No!

210
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:41,470
They passed by a while ago.

211
00:18:41,470 --> 00:18:42,920
They're not here anymore.

212
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,680
Not even in Sanji's room?!

213
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:47,390
Correct, there's some weird guy sleeping in there.

214
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:50,770
Oh yeah. I think I might know where they are.

215
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:54,570
It's outside, and there are no mirrors there.

216
00:18:54,570 --> 00:18:57,940
This morning, Luffy and Sanji-kun...

217
00:19:00,130 --> 00:19:01,660
fought at this place.

218
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:05,700
What?!

219
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:10,670
Luffy and Sanji had a fight?!

220
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,380
Why, why?!

221
00:19:13,830 --> 00:19:17,620
Sanji has his position in the Vinsmoke family.

222
00:19:18,710 --> 00:19:20,260
You're right.

223
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:23,850
He must have had a very good reason to come here.

224
00:19:23,850 --> 00:19:27,590
I don't think it'll be so easy to take him back!

225
00:19:29,020 --> 00:19:32,120
But, if we want to retrieve him,
we had better do it soon.

226
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:37,360
I was going to tell you once the whole group
was together, but I might as well tell you now.

227
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:41,320
When that ceremony begins tomorrow,

228
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:43,870
it will be anything but ordinary!

229
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:46,620
What do you mean?

230
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:51,080
You guys came here with Pekoms, didn't you?

231
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:53,080
Oh, Pekoms!

232
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:57,800
Is he all right?
We got separated from him on our way here!

233
00:19:56,130 --> 00:19:57,800
"Turn back"

234
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:03,200
Yeah, he's fine.
But there was a conspiratorial plot

235
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,760
that nearly succeeded in having him fed to some sharks.

236
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:07,310
A plot?

237
00:20:09,180 --> 00:20:11,420
If we hadn't spotted him,

238
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:16,020
he would be dead now.

239
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:26,830
A-Are you people...

240
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:29,080
monsters?

241
00:20:30,970 --> 00:20:35,750
How pathetic.
Barmaids shouldn't pass out from drinking.

242
00:20:41,930 --> 00:20:46,470
I wish they would've sent us
that girl from Sanji's crew.

243
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:52,020
Oh yeah! That girl named Nami, right?! I would've
loved to have a nice, headstrong girl like her here.

244
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:56,480
I heard that Big Mom has taken her prisoner.

245
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:59,820
Maybe we can negotiate a trade tomorrow.

246
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:11,750
Alright, that's enough drinking for tonight.
We can have our real party tomorrow night!

247
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:17,400
With the backing Emperor Big Mom,

248
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:21,050
Germa will once again rule the North Blue.

249
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:24,170
We will soon get our revenge

250
00:21:24,170 --> 00:21:32,640
on the hateful countries of the North Blue
who have insulted and scorned us.

251
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:36,000
Tomorrow will be the celebration!

252
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:48,560
I suppose that failure and shame of the Vinsmokes
turned out to have his uses after all.

253
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:53,010
That's true! Sanji was our bait,
and we were able to catch a big fish using him!

254
00:21:53,010 --> 00:21:58,830
When our enemies see Big Mom's flag
on Germa's fleet, they'll lose all desire to fight.

255
00:21:58,830 --> 00:22:03,510
We can conquer the seas
with greater power than ever before.

256
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:06,680
We ought to thank Sanji.

257
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:09,300
Thank Sanji?

258
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:14,730
To our failure!

259
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:16,600
To our beneficial punk!

260
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:19,140
Cheers!

261
00:22:23,230 --> 00:22:28,540
Don't let anyone come into contact
with the Vinsmokes until tomorrow's tea party.

262
00:22:28,540 --> 00:22:29,900
Understood.

263
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:32,950
Also, we've posted guards to Lady Reiju at

264
00:22:32,950 --> 00:22:34,330
the third-floor clinic.

265
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:37,000
Don't lower your guard.

266
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,000
Yes, sir.

267
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:41,220
The Vinsmokes can't escape their fate.

268
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,380
Don't say that out loud!

269
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,260
You idiot!

270
00:22:52,540 --> 00:22:54,260
Damn...

271
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:58,480
Those bastards!

272
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:54,200
Begone from my sight,
you miserable, lowlife pirate!

273
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,690
S-Sanji...

274
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:43,750
I didn't ask you to wait.

275
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,670
I refuse!

276
00:24:53,510 --> 00:24:55,220
Eat what you can.

277
00:24:57,860 --> 00:24:59,720
Food...

278
00:25:05,460 --> 00:25:10,690
I dropped it on my way here.
It's been crushed, and it got wet in the rain.

279
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:23,660
It's just another one of my failures, isn't it?

280
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:46,650
It's good!

281
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:03,040
This food's the best!

282
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:08,000
You put all of our favorites in here!

283
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:11,710
I want them to taste this!

284
00:26:14,930 --> 00:26:17,760
So good!

285
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:20,010
Yum! Yum!

286
00:26:20,940 --> 00:26:22,560
Liar!

287
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,040
Oh, that was so good!

288
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,360
I nearly shriveled up there!

289
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:38,040
If you're finished, then leave.

290
00:26:39,950 --> 00:26:42,280
What are talking about?! Come with us!

291
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:47,790
First of all:

292
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:54,220
I insulted the captain of my own ship,
who came all the way here to help me.

293
00:26:54,220 --> 00:26:57,970
And then I did my best to hurt him,
even though he didn't fight back at all.

294
00:27:00,180 --> 00:27:05,380
That means...
I cannot go back to the ship now.

295
00:27:10,330 --> 00:27:11,480
Second:

296
00:27:12,710 --> 00:27:17,190
That damn geezer who saved my life,
along with the home where I grew up,

297
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,260
the seafaring restaurant Baratie,

298
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:22,950
are both being held hostage
in case I don't play along.

299
00:27:25,620 --> 00:27:28,220
That means...

300
00:27:28,220 --> 00:27:31,460
I cannot escape from this wedding.

301
00:27:41,340 --> 00:27:42,730
Third:

302
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:47,080
My evil biological family
is walking into Big Mom's trap!

303
00:27:48,140 --> 00:27:51,270
They'll all be killed in a matter of hours!

304
00:27:55,620 --> 00:28:02,240
As long as you don't try to run away,
everything will work out just fine, Sanji.

305
00:28:07,950 --> 00:28:12,460
To my biological father,
older brothers, and my younger brother,

306
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:14,640
I have no obligation.

307
00:28:15,340 --> 00:28:17,760
I have nothing but resentment for those scumbags!

308
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:24,970
You're a failure who deserves to die!

309
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:28,810
Don't ever admit that I'm your father...

310
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:33,360
to even a single person!

311
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:36,670
I do not want anyone to learn of my shame.

312
00:28:39,930 --> 00:28:41,740
But I...

313
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:46,030
can't...

314
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:55,150
turn my back on them!

315
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:16,730
For those three reasons,
I can't go back with you guys!

316
00:29:26,110 --> 00:29:28,910
If you understand, get lost.

317
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:38,190
Tell me how you really feel!

318
00:30:52,420 --> 00:30:55,040
Sanji! Let's eat!

319
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:57,400
Just cook something, you fool!

320
00:30:57,400 --> 00:31:00,920
Sanji-kun, what are you gonna make today?

321
00:31:16,020 --> 00:31:18,890
Who stole all the food?!

322
00:31:19,650 --> 00:31:21,810
I knew it was you guys!

323
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:25,780
As your punishment, no dinner!

324
00:31:47,510 --> 00:31:51,090
Luffy... I...

325
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,400
I want to go back...

326
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:57,580
to the Sunny!

327
00:32:05,300 --> 00:32:10,950
But I can't find the courage...
to run away!

328
00:32:18,330 --> 00:32:23,310
Once the ceremony begins, I know...

329
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:27,000
that I won't be able to stop any of it on my own!

330
00:32:28,140 --> 00:32:30,660
I don't even consider...

331
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:34,980
those scumbags to be my family!

332
00:32:39,610 --> 00:32:40,770
But I...

333
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:46,090
want to save their lives!

334
00:32:55,070 --> 00:32:58,740
Well, that's who you are.

335
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:07,500
You've got us!
Let's crash this wedding!

